description.narrative: (i) Serve as a catalyst to support export and real sector growth in Ukraine during the EDP 2 implementation period (2006-2011) and beyond, by providing medium and long-term working capital and investment finance to Ukrainian private exporting enterprises. (ii) Further improve the ability of the Ukrainian banking sector to provide financial resources to the enterprise sector, through further development of intermediation, by expanding its depth and breadth through more and better lending products.

title.narrative: Share of subprojects/amounts financed through PBs participating in EDP2

comment.narrative: In view of the severe economic and security crisis in Ukraine that affects the willingness of banks to make new credit decisions,and the ability of Ukreximbank to take on additional exposure vis-a-vis other banks, this target may not be fully achieved.
Above is the percentage of credit line disbursed to sub-projects by participating banks. Also note the share of sub-projectsfinanced through PBs is 44.06%.

title.narrative: Medium and long term working capital and investment finance to private exporting enterprises

comment.narrative: Cumulative volume of disbursement to project beneficiary enterprises under EDP2 and AF.
Direct Project beneficiaries are private exporting companies.
The desired end-target is no non-performing sub-loans
Ukrexim reported 0 loans in substandard/doubtful/loss category under EDP2 at end-2013.
Given the severe economic crisis in Ukraine, this target may not be achieved.

Ukrexim reports 0.22 ROA according to UAS reporting standards at end-2013. This indicator is actually better than the average forthe banking system, which suffered from low profitability given the extended economic recession that started in 2012.
Indicator is a minimum desired figure based on annual 20% export growth in 2012-2014
Data provided is latest available as of July 2014, that is April 1, 2013 to March 31, 2014. Q2-2014 data not yet published byNational Bank.
